-The study finds that CMIP5 GCMs tend to underestimated the anthropogenic impacts on Amazonian precipitation. The authors conclude that the rainforest is likely to decline as rainfall lessens in southern Amazonia. But their model doesn't account for land surface feedback, which could be an important feature.},
