1930s, streamflow during the 20th century exceeded
average flows during the previous 200 years. The
drought of the 1930s resulted in the lowest flows
during the last three centuries, however, this
probably does not represent a worst-case scenario
for the Yellowstone as other climate reconstructions
indicate more extreme droughts prior to the 18th
