mode. This is supported by results from a
multicentury integration with a coupled ocean -
atmosphere general circulation model (CGCM) that
realistically simulates tropical Pacific decadal
variability. Finally, the sensitivity of the shallow
subtropical - tropical overturning cells to
greenhouse warming is discussed by analyzing the
results of a scenario integration with the same
CGCM.},
