add or subtract moisture. The large-scale moisture
budget divergences are more stable in time and
similar across reanalyses than model-based estimates
of E-P. Results are consistent with the view that
recycling of moisture is too large in most models
and the lifetime of moisture is too short. For the
energy cycle, most reanalyses have spurious
imbalances of similar to 10 W m(-2) within the
atmosphere, and similar to 5-10 W m(-2) in net
fluxes into the surface and to space. Major
improvements are needed in model treatment and
assimilation of moisture, and surface fluxes from
reanalyses should only be used with great caution.},
