performed. The detection variable is the ratio of 1
April snow water equivalent (SWE) to
water-year-to-date precipitation (P), chosen to
reduce the effect of P variability on the
results. Estimates of natural internal climate
variability are obtained from 1600 years of two
control simulations performed with fully coupled
