volcanic forcing likewise do not explain the SWE/P
reductions. The mean model estimate is that about
half of the SWE/P reductions observed in the west
from 1950 to 1999 are the result of climate changes
forced by anthropogenic greenhouse gases, ozone, and
aerosols.},
