geometry with thermal and eddy diffusion properties
appropriate to the atmosphere and the ocean and a
radiation condition at the top of the atmosphere
agrees with the observed spectrum. The difference in
power spectra between continental and marine
stations can be understood with this approach as a
consequence of the air mass above a maritime station
exchanging heat with both the atmosphere above and
the ocean below while a continental station
exchanges heat mostly with the atmosphere above. (C)
